rx_shadow_req.name: RX_SHADOW_REQ
desc: 1:Freeze stats CSRs so that all RX Stats values read from the registers will be from the same moment.
Note: The actual stats collection counters are not frozen, but because they are all read at the time of the freeze, they are cleared.

tx_shadow_req.name: TX_SHADOW_REQ
desc: 1:Freeze stats CSRs so that all TX Stats values read from the registers will be from the same moment.
Note that the actual stats collection counters are not frozen, but because they are all read at the time of the freeze, they are cleared

en_lf.name: EN_LF
desc: 0:The TX PCS does not respond to link faults
1:The TX PCS transmits link fault messages based on link faults detected by the RX

en_unidir.name: EN_UNIDIR
desc: 1:EHIP enables support for unidirectional link fault signaling as described in Clause 66
Remote faults have no impact on TX data, and Local faults will cause the TX to transmit Remote fault Ordered sets between frames

disable_rf.name: DISABLE_RF
desc: Send idles instead of remote faults for local faults in unidirectional mode
1:In unidirectional mode, local faults cause the TX to transmit Idles
0:In unidirectional mode, local faults cause the TX to transmit Remote Faults (spec default)

force_rf.name: FORCE_RF
desc: Force the TX MAC to transmit Remote Faults when link fault signaling is on
